  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "We should add the [`no-console`](https://eslint.org/docs/rules/no-console) rule to our eslint config. This will mean adding several `eslint-disable no-console`, but that's probably fine.\r\n\r\nThe alternative is to have a single module that we use for printing stuff to the console, and only that file would have the rule disabled. That way we can add temporary `console.log`s statements for debugging purposes and use this module for \"real\" logs.\r\n\r\nI prefer the second approach, even if it's a somewhat bigger change.",
